On Saturday, 9/26/20 I ordered a Cubano and a pork sandwich. The Cubano was identical to the pork sandwich. This was the saddest excuse of a Cubano sandwich I've ever encountered. A Cubano consists of ham, swiss cheese, pickles, mayo or mustard on Cuban bread. Instead this sandwich had shreds of pork and a few pickles on a hero bread. I ended up putting a slice of cheese and mayo to have some fullfillment of the real version. I'm disappointed in Lena Restaurant, and decided to look into other hispanic restaurants nearby that could do better.

I have ordered from Lena's on several occasions, I have also ate in, and picked up my orders. Today I'm sorry to say I will no longer patronize this business. I ordered via Grub Hub and specifically asked for my rice to be separated from my roast pork; I don't eat roast pork, but still wanted the rice. I noted this in the "special instructions" section. My order was placed and when I received it, the pork, rice and beans were all in the same container. When I called, the woman I spoke with admitted that it was busy and she overlooked the note, however, the way it was ordered was like a special where they do not separate the meat from the rice. Granted, I understand, but shouldn't someone have called me. She continuously said, "sorry, we are very, very, very busy today". Let me see if I can speak with my manager. She comes back on the phone indictaing there is nothing she can do, but I bet she didn't tell him she overlooked my message. I wasn't asking for a new meal, simply a side of white rice could have remedied the situation, if not today, perhaps if I when I placed an order in the future. No matter how good the food is, poor customer service can make or break a customer. Not to mention,  I had the food delivered to my house, because I'm pregnant and wasn't up to coming out in the heat only to be disappointed. I will be certain to stop by and pay them a visit when I'm in the neighborhood, but as of now, I'm done with Lena's.

I used to work by 207th street in Manhattan and would have endless options of wonderful Dominican food there. Since I got a job transfer, I was craving some good Dominican food. Thankfully, this place opened up just in my neighborhood where we used to have a failing pizza shop. Their food is excellent. Always fresh and tasty. If you're craving some good Dominican food at a fair price, look no further.
